txt.en: 'A few of my Rangers are wounded, but no deaths. Rûkhor surely could have taken us all out if he wished. Is he toying with us?'
Instance: Ambush at Echad Taerdim
Talk to Mablung
'You are not fine, and you are lucky I have experience with the spiders of Mirkwood.'
'Let this attack be a warning, Men of Gondor.'
'Push them back! These uruks are no match for the Rangers of Ithilien!'
'You say that like I'm some helpless babe! I'm fine!'
'That is enough. Return to me, Bloodless.'
The camp is under attack!
The uruks fall back!
Talk to Legolas
Travel to Echad Taerdim with Legolas and Atli
'Interfere in my plans, and the Bloodless will destroy you.'
'It seems we are not alone with the spiders in this place. Is everyone all right?'
Defend the camp
'Cirith Ungol is my domain, and you are not welcome.'
'Bratha Tasakh, do you desire the freedom of the Ungoladan in their keeping?'
'What now? Spiders?'
TBD
'No, I hear the clash of steel upon steel. We must hurry!'
You return to Mablung's camp with Legolas and Atli, but something is wrong.
A few of my Rangers are wounded, but no deaths. Rûkhor surely could have taken us all out if he wished. Is he toying with us?
Rûkhor and his forces depart
'Hold. I hear something ahead. The camp is under attack!'
Legolas would like to return to Echad Taerdim.\n\nYou should travel with Legolas and Atli to the Ranger camp.
'Come, [placeholder], let us deliver Atli to the care of the Rangers.'
'Hmph.'
'He is no longer one of us. He can die at the hands of these outsiders.'
Strange uruks are attacking the Ranger camp.\n\nDefend the camp!
'You are lucky too, that I was the one to come to your aid. Their venom can be deadly.'
The uruks have fallen back, but a strange man has appeared above the camp.\n\nYou should listen to Rûkhor.
'Hmm. As you wish.'
Legolas would like to return to Echad Taerdim.\n\nYou should talk to Legolas.
TBD Instance
The attack has been repelled.\n\nYou should talk to Mablung.
'Come, [placeholder], let us deliver Atli to the care of the Rangers.'
Listen to Rûkhor
'Come, we must tend to the wounded and assess the damage to the camp.'
